Joint-It Slurry Primer Bag - High Adhesion Slurry Primer for Paving (20kg)
item.g:description: Are you looking for a high strength priming slurry for your porcelain, natural stone or concrete paving slabs ?Joint-It Slurry Primer is an exceptional bonding agent, creating a super strength adhesion between your paving slabs and the base underneath. What is slurry primer used for? This paving primer is applied to the back of the paving slab before laying it onto the concrete base. The slurry primer serves as a bonding agent, allowing the paving material to adhere securely to the base, creating a smooth, strong and durable surface. It fills in any cracks or pores on the base, creating a smooth and even substrate for the paving slab.Quick to apply with a brush or roller, this paving slurry only requires one coat.Overall, priming slurry is a crucial component in the paving process, providing an effective, cost-efficient solution to create a strong, durable, and long-lasting surface. With its numerous benefits, it is an excellent choice for any paving project, whether small or large in scale.

item.g:title: Joint-It Slurry Primer - High Adhesion Slurry Primer for Paving (17KG)
item.g:description: Are you looking for a high strength priming slurry for your porcelain, natural stone or concrete paving slabs ?Joint-It Slurry Primer is an exceptional bonding agent, creating a super strength adhesion between your paving slabs and the base underneath. What is slurry primer used for? This paving primer is applied to the back of the paving slab before laying it onto the concrete base. The slurry primer serves as a bonding agent, allowing the paving material to adhere securely to the base, creating a smooth, strong and durable surface. It fills in any cracks or pores on the base, creating a smooth and even substrate for the paving slab.Quick to apply with a brush or roller, this paving slurry only requires one coat.Overall, priming slurry is a crucial component in the paving process, providing an effective, cost-efficient solution to create a strong, durable, and long-lasting surface. With its numerous benefits, it is an excellent choice for any paving project, whether small or large in scale.

10mm Stone - Bulk Bag (1000kg)
item.g:description: If you are looking for a versatile and durable material for your construction or landscaping project, look no further than our 10mm stone bulk bag. This bag contains small stones that are ideal for mixing with cement and sand to create strong concrete and screed. You can also use them for backfilling drains and pipes, or for creating attractive features or borders in your garden, path or driveway.
item.g:product_type: Home > Paving Essentials > Aggregates > Gravels & Chippings

item.g:title: Ballast - Bulk Bag (1000kg)
item.g:description: A 1000kg ballast bulk bag is a large bag that contains a mixture of sand and stone ballast, which is used for concreting and other building projects. Ballast is also known as all-in ballast, because it contains both fine and coarse aggregates. Some of the benefits of using a ballast bulk bag are: It is easy to transport and store, as it comes in a single bag that can be lifted by a crane or forklift. It is versatile and can be used for various purposes, such as providing a stable base for driveways, shed bases, fence posts, and more. It is resistant to fire and can withstand high temperatures. It is economical and can save you money on buying separate bags of sand and stone.
item.g:product_type: Home > Paving Essentials > Aggregates > Building Aggregates

item.g:title: Crushed Concrete - Bulk Bag (1000kg)
item.g:description: A 1000kg crushed concrete Bulk Bag is a convenient and cost-effective way to use recycled concrete for your construction projects. Crushed concrete is a type of recycled aggregate that is made from demolished buildings, sidewalks, roads, and other concrete structures. It is crushed and screened to remove dirt and debris, and then graded by size to suit different applications.Some of the benefits of using crushed concrete are: It is cheaper than natural aggregate and reduces the need for mining new materials. It is environmentally friendly and helps to reduce landfill waste and carbon emissions. It is durable and strong, and can withstand harsh weather conditions and heavy loads.
item.g:product_type: Home > Paving Essentials > Aggregates > Building Aggregates

item.g:title: Soft / Builders Sand - Bulk Bag (1000kg)
item.g:description: A soft sand bulk bag is a large bag of fine-grained sand that is ideal for various building and landscaping projects. Soft sand, also known as building sand or bricklayer’s sand, is a versatile material that can be used for mortar, plastering, rendering, and screeding. Soft sand is easy to work with and has good water retention properties.
item.g:product_type: Home > Paving Essentials > Aggregates > Building Aggregates

item.g:title: Type 1 MOT - Bulk Bag (1000kg)
item.g:description: A Type 1 MOT – Bulk Bag is a large bag of crushed stone that can be used as a sub-base for various construction projects. It is also known as DOT Type 1, MOT Type 1, or simply Type 1. It is made from limestone, granite, or other hard materials that are crushed to a uniform size of 40mm or less. The fine particles fill the gaps between the larger ones, creating a strong and stable layer that can support heavy loads.
item.g:product_type: Home > Paving Essentials > Aggregates > Building Aggregates

item.g:title: Premium Top Soil - Bulk Bag (1000kg)
item.g:description: If you are looking for a high-quality top soil for your garden, look no further than the Premium Top Soil Bulk Bag. This product is ideal for creating new beds and borders, improving existing soil, or laying turf.

item.g:title: London Yellow Reclaimed 55mm Handmade Bricks (Pack of 540)
item.g:description: Our London Yellow Reclaimed 55mm Handmade Bricks are a great choice for matching properties across London and the South East of England. London Yellow Reclaimed 55mm Handmade Bricks are one our most popular bricks and are perfect for building walls as well as garden projects.These yellow reclaimed bricks are used as a main form of building material and are still very much in evidence in properties across London and the South East of England. Colours do vary slightly from weathered and darker colours to some much brighter shades known as canary yellows.There is also the chance that you will find flecks of ash which discolour the bricks due to the ash in the clay turning black when fired.
